      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has slightly softened, add a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>and the <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pot with the <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>and<strong> </strong>the <strong>smoked paprika</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>remaining white wine vinegar</strong> and the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for a final 4-5 min or until thickened to a jam-like consistency – this is your <strong>vindaloo-style chutney</strong></p>",
